## Display Types

#### Display : Flex
   - Elements are positioned next to each other
   - Container will display on a block level


#### Display : Inline-Flex
   - Elements are positioned next to each other
   - Container will change to Inline Level
   - If items elements are bigger than parent container they will shrink to fit.




<img src="image-kxgznnaf.png" width="500px">




## Vertical & Horizontal Positioning

### Justify Content
###### Controls alignment of all items on the main(horizontal) axis.

> - justify-content

```sass
/* Horizontaly align the content to the end of the container */
justify-content: flex-start;
```


### Align Items
###### Controls alignment of all items on the main(horizontal) axis, single row elements only.

> - align-items

```sass
/* Vertically align the content to the end of the container */
align-items: flex-end;
```
  if possible, the items will stretch from top to bottom of the container (this        is the default value; elements with a specified height will not stretch;            elements with a minimum height or no height specified will stretch).


### Align Content
###### Controls alignment of all items on the main(horizontal) axis, multiple row elements.

> - align-items

```sass
/* Vertically align all elements to the end of the container */
align-content: flex-end;
```




## Container Positioning


### Flex Direction
###### Sets how flex items are placed in the flex container defining the main axis and the direction (normal or reversed).

:::note 
When changing the direction, the main and cross axis interchange as well as the functions related to those. 
::: 

> - flex-direction

```sass
/* Position from left to right across the container starting from the top left */
flex-direction: flex-start; <- (def)

/* Position from right to left across the container starting from the top right corner */
flex-direction: flex-end;

/* Position from top to bottom of the container starting from the top left corner. */
flex-direction: column;

/* Position from the bottom to the top of the container starting from the bottom left corner */
flex-direction: column-reverse;
```


## Container Wrapping


### Flex Wrap
###### Sets how flex items are placed in the flex container defining the main axis and the direction (normal or reversed).



```sass
/* Position from left to right across the container starting from the top left */
flex-wrap: nowrap; <- (def)

/* Position from right to left across the container starting from the top right corner */
flex-wrap: wrap;

/* Position from top to bottom of the container starting from the top left corner. */
flex-wrap: wrap-reverse;

```
